We recommended that Management:
Allow only duly bonded officers to collect money for the government or apply proper bonding of additional designated collecting officers pursuant to Treasury Circular No. 02-2009;
Increase the fidelity bond of accountable officers whose collections require a greater accountability;
Require accountable officers to remit their collections daily to the Municipal Treasurer and record their collections daily in the Cashbook;
Enjoin the Municipal Treasurer to deposit collections/remittances with authorized government depository bank/s daily or not later than the next banking day; and
Conform to the prescribed procedures under COA Circular No. 92-382 dated July 3, 1992 in the recording, turnover and deposit of collections and remittances.

We recommended that Management:
Appoint a duly licensed MSWDO whose primary task is to assist children in conflict with the law;
Include  a representative from the youth sector in the LCPC as provided for under Sec. 15 of RA 9344;
Empower the LCPC to focus on the development and implementation of a Comprehensive Local Juvenile Intervention Program pursuant to RA 9344 and DILG Memorandum Circular No. 2012-120; and
Set aside an amount or partner with private individuals or NGOs licensed and accredited by the DSWD to build a Youth Detention Home for the protection and welfare of the children/youth.

We recommended that management:
Submit immediately to the Office of the Auditor all contracts due for review and evaluation pursuant to COA Circular No. 2009-001;
Strictly observe the reglementary period of within five working days from execution of the contract in the submission of contracts for review, copies of purchase orders and all the required pertinent documents;
Establish a monitoring system/tool that contains basic information about the projects to be undertaken and procurement timelines, and will serve as guide and reference for checking and evaluating the progress of the projects; and
Prepare and submit the Procurement Monitoring Report prescribed by GPPB Circular No. 03-2005 copy furnished the COA Auditor for information.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Accountant to:
Strictly observe the reglementary period provided under COA Circular No. 2009-006;
Coordinate with the employees concerned, especially with the Municipal Treasurer’s Office in the preparation of documents and install necessary measures for the complete submission and prompt consolidation of vouchers;
Submit the vouchers, reports and supporting documents for the periods July to November 2017 for GF, SEF and TF and for the periods October to November 2017 for TCC for our verification and audit.
We further recommended that Management cause the suspension of the salaries of concerned officials and employees until they shall have submitted the required documents to COA pursuant to Section 122 of PD 1445.

We recommended that Management:
Locate all the source documents and MOA/Trust Agreements with the source agencies to review the terms and conditions corresponding to the funds transferred in relation to the implementation of programs and projects;
Return to the source agency or remit to the Bureau of Treasury any unused/unexpended balance if so stipulated in the MOA/Trust Agreement and furnish COA with copies of JEV taking up the return or remittance;
Designate a focal person who would be responsible in monitoring the status of project implementation of funds transferred from source agencies, be it an NGA, a GOCC or an LGU; and
Furnish COA with copies of the source documents of the funds previously transferred, the MOA/Trust Agreements with source agencies, and Office Order of the designated focal person, within fifteen (days) from receipt hereof.

We recommended that Management:
Empower and direct the designated focal persons and Barangay Captains to specify and initiate projects in accordance with the approved budget and to closely work with the engineering department for assistance in the preparation of the appropriate program of works;
Enforce due dates for the submission of the project proposals after the approval of the budget to fast-track the implementation;
Create effective measures to monitor the project implementation and require close coordination between the BAC and MPDC in the time and manner of procurement, and with the MEO in the execution, providing technical support where necessary; and
Maximize available human resources in each concerned departments, stop the renewal of job order personnel (JOs) who are non-performing and hire instead Jos with needed technical qualifications to best deliver the desired goals and outcomes of the Municipality.

We recommended that Management:
Observe the prescribed allocation of at least five percent (5%) of the total LGU budget appropriations in the preparation of the GAD Plan and Budget and make necessary amendments in the existing Budget pursuant to PCW-DBM-DILG-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01;
Direct and empower the designated focal person to manage the implementation of projects in accordance with the approved plan and  budget and to closely work with the concerned department/s to assist in the preparation of the appropriate plans and programs;
Impose timelines and observe schedules in the execution and procurement of projects, and supplement additional technical staff where necessary.

We have recommended to the management for executive action:

Creation of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board in accordance with the provision of law;

The plan should be reviewed and updated as required by law to ensure its sustainability, relevance and effectiveness;

Campaigns should be collaborated with the barangay officials concerned;

Continued and stricter implementation of waste segregation, and thorough collection of waste based on set schedules; and;

Provide budget for the purchase of sanitary landfill.

We have recommended the following:
The Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit Bank Reconciliation Statements monthly in adherence to Section 74 of PD 1445 and COA Circular No. 96-11. Also require her to get the monthly bank statements from the depository bank promptly and regularly;
The Municipal Treasurer to reconcile his cashbooks entries with that from the accounting records at least quarterly;
The Collecting Officer to submit the Report of Collections and Deposits to the accounting division.

We have recommended the following to the Municipal Treasurer:
Adhere strictly with the regulation to ensure effective performance on the task assigned;
Submit monthly report of collections and report of accountable forms;
Turnover the used and issued accountable forms in sequence.

